videos.name: Charming 2-bedroom flat to rent in Camden
videos.description:
**The homely heaven**

_Because nothing is more welcoming than this_

**Will I like it here?**

It would be hard not to.

Looking for a stylish flat near Camden Town? 

You've come to the right place.

**Really? Tell me more...**

You will love the charming living room. It has carpeted floors, cool grey walls, and beautiful decor. There are comfy sofas for movie nights, and a dining table for meals. It's the perfect spot to relax after a long day.

We think it’s ideal for an easy-going group looking for a little fun. Camden Town is a little over 15 minutes' away on foot, and is home to a huge range of trendy bars, shops and markets. The beautiful Caledonian Park is even closer.

**Your top 3 reasons to live here:**

- The living room is comfortable and beautifully decorated.
- The kitchen and bathroom are sleek and modern.
- You're just over 15 minutes' on foot from Camden Town.

**But you need to know this...**

- This flat is on the 1st floor of the building, which doesn't have an elevator — there's a little extra exercise for your day.

**Your Home-checker, Jonatan, said:**

_“I loved this property. It’s a really beautiful and modern property."_

**Help me make up my mind...**

This is a charming 1st floor, 2-bedroom flat on South Villas, London. It boasts a stylish living room with beautifully welcoming furnishings, and a modern kitchen and bathroom.

This property is ideal for a fun-loving group or family looking for a laid-back spot close to the action. You can enjoy the peace of a residential area, near the vibrant Camden Town and Kentish Town.

apartments.title: Gorgeous 1-bedroom flat to rent in Kensington & Chelsea
apartments.address: A Ossington St, London W2 4LY, UK

videos.name: Gorgeous 1-bedroom flat to rent in Kensington & Chelsea
videos.description:
Want to live among London’s rich and famous? If so, this gorgeous 1-bedroom flat is available to rent on Ossington Street in Kensington & Chelsea. On the first floor, this quaint apartment has been beautifully decorated in a modern, yet minimalist design. White walls and large windows make the property bright and inviting. Walking into the flat, you’ll find a lovely sofa and armchair in the living space, which will come in handy when you have friends coming over for some tea. There is also a dining table and flatscreen TV. Right next to the living space, you’ll encounter the fully equipped kitchen. It is hard to stumble upon a kitchen of this quality in London. With an oven, stove, microwave, dishwasher, coffeemaker, and a tea kettle, you will be ready to prepare delicious meals or bake some scrumptious desserts. Plenty of cabinet space is also available. We loved the tile floors. Moving into the bedroom, you will find a double bed with a nightstand. Plus, you’ll have plenty of storage for clothes and other belongings with the standalone wardrobe and chest of drawers. Finally, the bathroom, with beautiful tile work, has a bath/shower, sink, and toilet. You will also find on the property a washing machine and dryer.

It does not get any better than living here. This neighbourhood is in the heart of London. Brush shoulders with the Royals as you will be a stone’s throw away from the Kensington Palace and Gardens. Dream of starring in the next Julia Roberts and Hugh Grant film? Well, you are also close to Notting Hill, one of London’s most beloved districts. Public transport is extremely accessible here and you’ll find plenty of places to buy groceries, including the famous Portobello Market.

videos.name: Sunny studio flat to rent close to Mile End Park in Tower Hamlets
videos.description:
This minimalist studio flat on Burdett Road is located on the top floor of an older building, under a mansard roof, which has a lot of character. Of course, the older building means there isn’t an elevator, so you’ll get all the exercise you need without joining the gym! The entrance hall divides the studio into two parts. On one side is the modern bathroom, which has a bathtub, and through which you can access a spacious terrace. To the other side of the hall is the living space. It has 2 glass doors that open to a balcony overlooking the street. It’s a fabulous space and very minimalist. The kitchen isn’t equipped, but has all the major appliances. The rest of the room is furnished with a bed and a small desk. 

In east London, your studio flat in Tower Hamlets is located right on the edge of Mile End Park. This is a sprawling space with paths to stroll or jog. The park also has lots of activities to keep you busy. There is a climbing wall, a karting track, leisure center and an outdoor stadium. You can cut through the park and arrive at Queen Mary University in 10 minutes. Mideastern cuisine is served up at multiple restaurants along your street, and there are plenty of bars and pubs closer to the school. You can pick up every day groceries at the Nica Local. It’s beside the post office just 3 minutes away.
